Political Capital[b1]: The Hungarian Guard increases the risk in the country
According to the Risk Analysis Division of the Political Capital Policy Division, the activities of the Hungarian Guard, constituted in August of this year with the support of the Better Hungary Movement, have increased from a number of points of view the political risk of Hungary and the region.
The company's "risk warning" states: in relation to the Hungarian Guard's activity, the biggest political risk is that "with the worsening of the ethnic tensions between the Roma and non-Gypsian populations in Hungary, even in the short term, violent ethnic clashes may occur".
The main reason for this is that the political strategy of the Hungarian Guard is likely to provoke an event of this nature - he added the representative of the Research Institute.
They said that all this was due to one of the main shortcomings of Hungarian political life's protagonists: "The protagonists of public life gave the public debate on the gypsy problem to representatives of radical and extremist political groups, who were able to base their political strategy on the differences between gypsies and Hungarians."
This exacerbates the problem, makes normal dialogue impossible, strengthens extremists and increases the likelihood of the outbreak of violent conflicts - they estimate.
Moreover, according to the Institute of Research, the activities of the National Guard, as a result of the high attention of the national and international media, "has significantly deteriorated Hungary's image abroad, especially as regards the country's stability and democratic development".
