Congress approves the transposition of the Mifid, which entered into force on 1 November
In parallel with its parliamentary procedure, which ended today with the Congress's vote on the amendments incorporated into the draft in the Senate, the Government has submitted to the public hearing the regulation that will develop the new law, with the aim of both entering into force before the end of the year.
The representatives of the various groups agreed to highlight the efforts made by Members and Senators to negotiate and consensualize the best regulation in the fields of ensuring the protection of investors and to regulate in detail the activity of entities for the efficient functioning of markets.
The Mifid, which amends the Securities Markets Act, involves modernising financial markets, while strengthening investor protection, improving the supervisory powers of the National Securities Market Commission (CNMV) and fostering cooperation between the various European Union supervisors.
The new regulation will enable financial advisory services to be provided to both specialized firms and natural or legal persons and will create a new type of financial services signatures (ESIS), financial advisory companies (AFI), which join securities companies, securities agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it expands the number of financial instruments operating systems so that regulated secondary markets are joined by multilateral trading systems and order internalization systems, which will compete with the current stock exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment service companies to disclose on the market information on the key aspects of their business profile, exposure to risk and risk management forms and requires them to keep a record of all the operations they are carrying out to facilitate supervision by the CNMV.
In its move by the Congress Economic Commission, several amendments were incorporated, including emphasising that titled debt is considered as a "complex" financial instrument given its high risk to the investor, which has been demonstrated with the US high risk mortgage debt (subprime).
In addition, the transposition of the directive was used to legally delimit the functions that diplomats in Economics and Entrepreneurs can perform 30 years after the real decree delimiting the professional functions reserved for economists was adopted in 1977.
